    "154008369": {
      "title": "Emotional ownership: the next generation's relationship with the family firm. Fam",
      "abstract": "“The Next Generations” in family firms are the key to the survival of the sector, yet gaps remain in the knowledge about their relationship with the firm. This research focuses on the determinants ..."
    },
    "146422931": {
      "title": "Understanding the emotional dynamics of family enterprises",
      "abstract": "The importance of emotional dynamics in familybusiness systems is studied in two case studies of small, highly similar,British family firms dealing with the transfer of managerial power andleadership from the second to the third generation.Twenty-three in-depthinterviews were conducted with members of each family business system between1994 and 1998. The first family managed to negotiate the generationalpower shift but watched the business stagnate afterward, while the secondfamily failed to make progress in the transfer of leadership and suffered thedeparture of the son. Patterns in the families' emotional functioning in the family, business, andownership sub-systems are then discussed.Families in business shouldexpect to be faced with chronic anxiety during inevitable transition periodsand should explore succession solution options that are feasible and acceptableto key stakeholders instead of adopting untested solutions. (SAA)"
    }
